Great release and thanx a lot for this awesome work!

I have some questions regarding the RD-0120 engine configuration (from BobCat's soviet engine pack, which is supported by RO):

- This engine has a possible min. throttle of 55%, not 45% (according to the german wikipedia entry) ... ??? ...

But what puzzles me is the fuel mixture rating:

RO says: 27.5% liq. oxygen and 72.5% liq. hydrogen. I know, that these numbers are MASS ratios. But...

The mixture ratio is 6:1. Means: 6 parts hydrogen AND one part oxygen -> 7 parts.

1/7 = 0.142857

Oxygen has nearly exactly 16 times the mass of hydrogen so by multiplying it with 16 I get 2.285714

Or in percentage: 22.9% liq oxygen and 77.1% liq. hydrogen.

Those numbers are quite different...

For the russian Energija rocket the weight difference would be roughly 115 tons. I know that you guys put much more effort and competence in those configurations and maths than I, so I ask humbly, what I calculated wrong. What have I missed?

When I select "revert to VAB, the game crashes. I've had it happen repeatedly, with different craft, at different times; on the pad, in flight, after splashdown.

In the output log, it says "KSP.exe caused an Access Violation (0xc0000005)

in module KSP.exe at 0023:016d7b3a." and "Write to location 00000000 caused an access violation."

I'm not sure how to post the whole log, but this appears in each one.

I can confirm this.
